  "text": "We include a model of the afferent input that drives these DINs. This \"afferent model\" is upstream from the DIN models and simulates the afferent activity generated by antennal hair fields. Hair fields are insect-specific patches of external mechanoreceptors which, because of their location, function as proprioceptors. Our model simulates known properties of antennal hair field afferents, which can encode antennal joint angle and angular velocity owing to their phasic-tonic response characteristics [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The objective of the afferent model is to test how much of the DIN response properties can be explained by a single type of mechanoreceptor afferents.",
